The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Fifteen boys, to be chosen from a 30-member pool at a football camp, will travel to Arsenal Academy to participate in a two-week long training session to be held in August. The 30 boys for the camp will be selected from the May 17 final of the Tata Tea Arsenal Soccer Stars tournament.           
	 Sporting Union reached the final of the A.N. Ghosh Trophy after they were declared winners of the first semi-final against East Bengal by virtue of a first-innings lead. The match was awarded to them since there was no supply of new balls after 100 overs of play. Later, Sporting Union lodged a complaint against East Bengal for alleged ball tampering.                 
	 Satrajit Lahiri has been named fielding coach for the Indian University side at the National Cricket Academy. The conditioning camp for the players will begin on May 12.                 
	 Burdwan will meet Rakhi Sangha in the boys semi-finals of the 25th junior state basketball championship at the 1923 Chhatra Samity ground on Thursday.                 
	 Souvik Chakraborty, Rupankar Nath, Joydeep Dutta and Anjan Mallick have been selected to represent Bengal in the National B chess championship slated to be held in Goa from September 15. 
                                                                                                                                                                     
